            <title>[FLINK-22683] The total Flink/process memory of memoryConfiguration in /taskmanagers can be null or incorrect value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-22683</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14435&quot; title=&quot;Add TaskManageResourceInfo which match the memory compositions of taskmanager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-14435&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-14435&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we add the `memoryConfiguration` to /taskmanagers REST API. However, that field can be `null` if it is not configured by the user or the incorrect value in fine-grained resource management. We need to calculate them proactively.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
